      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Embracing the futility of resisting the inevitable might bring temporary solace, but it would also mean surrendering to helplessness. You're already aware of the world's problems; fighting against them, even in the face of despair, is a testament to your own resilience. Excessive self-harm is not growth, but rather a sign of emotional exhaustion; it's a cry for attention in a world that already seems numb to the pain.",
